32	/*! \file
33	    \brief A GEMM example using CUTLASS for the NVIDIA Blackwell SM100 architecture.
34	
35	    This example demonstrates a simple way to instantiate and run a blockscaled NVFP4 GEMM on the NVIDIA Blackwell SM100 architecture.
36	
37	    The Blackwell SM100 CUTLASS kernel uses the new Block Scaled Tensor Core MMA Instructions (tcgen05.mma.blockscaled) introduced
38	    on the Blackwell architecture (sm100a) which have 2x throughput compared to fp8 Tensor Core MMA instructions (tcgen05.mma)
39	    and 4x throughput compared to fp8 Hopper Tensor Core MMA Instructions (WGMMA) (See https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/parallel-thread-execution).
40	
41	    Similar to 70_blackwell_gemm, this kernel leverages:
42	    1. Per-SM memory called Tensor Memory (TMEM)  (Please refer to CUDA 12.8 docs on https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/).
43	
44	    2. The extended warp-specialized kernel design introduced in Hopper enabled by use of TMEM
45	    which allows us to decouple the execution of MMA and epilogue into separate warps.
46	
47	    3. A new SW controlled dynamic scheduler based on cluster launch control (See https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/parallel-thread-execution).
48	
49	    Usage:
50	
51	      $ ./examples/72_blackwell_narrow_precision_gemm/72a_blackwell_nvfp4_bf16_gemm --m=2048 --n=2048 --k=2048
52	*/
